  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Joint Global Health Trials Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UK Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC) funds outstanding global health research through the National Institute for Health Research (NIHR). This programme is administered by the UK Medical Research Council (MRC), which reports activities under the UK Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS). NIHR disburses funds to MRC, which makes onwards disbursements to awardees. The aim of this programme is to generate new knowledge to contribute to improving health in low and middle income countries (LMICs). Priority will be given to proposals most likely to yield implementable results and designed to address the major causes of mortality or morbidity in LMICs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To fund rigorous research to produce implementable evidence addressing questions of major importance to mortality and morbidity in low- and middle-income countries.</narrative>
  </description>
